summary: An ordinance submitting to the qualified voters of the City of Seattle, at the general election to be held in such city on Tuesday, March 4, 1919, the proposition for the creation of an indebtedness in the sum of Nine Hundred Thousand Dollars ($900,000) by the issuance and sale of general, negotiable, interest bearing coupon bonds of the City of Seattle in said amount, for the construction of a bridge across the West Waterway at West Spokane Street in said city.
